## Look up Existing SubnetGroup Resource {#look-up}

Get an existing SubnetGroup resource's state with the given name, ID, and optional extra properties used to qualify the lookup.
<div>
<pulumi-chooser type="language" options="csharp,go,typescript,python,yaml,java"></pulumi-chooser>
</div>

## Import



Using `pulumi import`, import DB Subnet groups using the `name`. For example:

```sh
$ pulumi import aws:rds/subnetGroup:SubnetGroup default production-subnet-group
```


To learn more about importing existing cloud resources, see [Importing resources](/docs/using-pulumi/adopting-pulumi/import/).
